MARY: <i>Never.
You just heard my voice.</i>

11:54.116 --> 11:55.951
(IN A DEEP VOICE) Which was
quite a few octaves lower

11:55.951 --> 11:57.347
than the voice
you're used to hearing.

11:57.347 --> 11:59.354
- DINAH: Really?
- Yes. Sexy Sam.

11:59.354 --> 12:01.689
DINAH: That's funny.
They never saw your face?

12:01.689 --> 12:03.024
MARY: (IN NORMAL VOICE)
<i>Never saw my face.</i>

12:03.024 --> 12:04.292
The most frustrating thing...

12:04.292 --> 12:05.828
- DINAH: That's not fair!
- ...that I ever experienced.

12:05.828 --> 12:06.962
- DINAH: Well, are you--
- Yes, it was

12:06.962 --> 12:08.931
because this would've been
such a letdown.

12:08.931 --> 12:10.131
- You--
- That's not a sexy face.

12:10.131 --> 12:11.700
- Yes. Oh, tell them.
- Is this it?

12:11.700 --> 12:15.040
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

12:19.110 --> 12:21.976
MARY: <i>She became
every male viewer's fantasy.</i>

12:21.976 --> 12:26.014
<i>And there was big hype about her
because the producers decided</i>

12:26.014 --> 12:30.986
<i>to create some interest
by not revealing who she was.</i>

12:30.986 --> 12:35.558
<i>Now I was making,
for each episode, 85 dollars,</i>

12:35.558 --> 12:36.991
<i>and I decided that</i>

12:36.991 --> 12:39.261
<i>because of all the attention
that the character was getting,</i>

12:39.261 --> 12:40.795
<i>that I should go in
and ask for more.</i>

12:40.795 --> 12:42.464
<i>And I did. I went
into the producer's office</i>

12:42.464 --> 12:45.034
<i>and I said, "I really,
really think that I should get</i>

12:45.034 --> 12:47.302
<i>a little more money
for this role that I'm playing."</i>

12:47.302 --> 12:50.305
<i>And without letting me
finish the sentence, he said,</i>

12:50.305 --> 12:53.708
<i>"Do you know, my dear,
anybody with a good pair of legs</i>

12:53.708 --> 12:55.711
<i>and a sultry voice
can play this part</i>

12:55.711 --> 12:57.679
<i>so goodbye
and good luck to you."</i>

12:57.679 --> 12:58.914
♪ (ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

12:58.914 --> 13:05.154
<i>♪ Ten cents a dance
That's what they pay me ♪</i>

13:05.154 --> 13:11.459
<i>♪ Gosh, how they weigh me down ♪</i>

13:11.459 --> 13:18.528
<i>♪ Ten cents a dance
Softies and rough guys ♪</i>

13:18.703 --> 13:24.205
<i>♪ Tough guys who tear my gown ♪</i>

13:24.205 --> 13:26.208
DINAH: Did you ever start out
like everybody else,

13:26.208 --> 13:29.712
having frustrations and periods
when you couldn't get...

13:29.712 --> 13:30.979
- Oh.
- ...couldn't get arrested?

13:30.979 --> 13:32.381
- Many, many.
- DINAH: Really?

13:32.381 --> 13:34.383
And when I could get arrested,
it was on a television show

13:34.383 --> 13:37.686
that was probably
really very badly done.

13:37.686 --> 13:40.656
Carrying microfilm
of government property

13:40.656 --> 13:42.685
- is illegal.
- (GASPS)

13:42.685 --> 13:46.093
You're under arrest,
suspicion of espionage.

13:46.093 --> 13:48.691
- Vern, you can take her in now.
- ♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

13:48.691 --> 13:50.232
MARY: <i>I did a lot
of those boring shows.</i>

13:50.232 --> 13:51.933
- ♪ (WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- DINAH: <i>I never heard of any job</i>

13:51.933 --> 13:53.102
<i>you didn't get.</i>

13:53.102 --> 13:54.770
Well, there was one part
I didn't get

13:54.770 --> 13:56.071
and I'm really very glad
I didn't.

13:56.071 --> 13:58.339
It was to play the part
of Danny Thomas's daughter.

13:58.339 --> 14:00.509
- (AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)
- Now, ladies and gentlemen,

14:00.509 --> 14:01.777
a formal introduction please,

14:01.777 --> 14:04.046
for our guest star,
Mary Tyler Moore.

14:04.046 --> 14:09.250
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

14:09.250 --> 14:11.987
A few years ago, we auditioned
a lot of young girls

14:11.987 --> 14:14.690
to play the part
of my older daughter, Terry,

14:14.690 --> 14:15.724
in the family series.

14:15.724 --> 14:18.360
And Mary was one
of the two finalists.

14:18.360 --> 14:20.929
But it was left to me
to have to tell her

14:20.929 --> 14:22.798
that she wasn't right
for the part.

14:22.798 --> 14:25.801
- (SIGHS)
- And I'd like you to see

14:25.801 --> 14:27.903
why she wasn't right
for the part.

14:27.903 --> 14:30.172
- Come here.
- (CLEARS THROAT)

14:30.172 --> 14:34.877
- (AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
- Now, tell the truth.

14:34.877 --> 14:36.979
Would anybody believe
that that nose

14:36.979 --> 14:38.581
could be the father
of that nose?

14:38.581 --> 14:40.515
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

14:40.515 --> 14:42.751
The day that I read
for the part of Laura Petrie

14:42.751 --> 14:44.853
- on <i>The Dick Van Dyke Show...
- ♪</i> (GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING) <i>♪</i>

14:44.853 --> 14:48.223
...had followed a week
of rejections,

14:48.223 --> 14:50.726
and I was having coffee
with a friend,

14:50.726 --> 14:52.360
and my agent tracked me down
and said,

14:52.360 --> 14:54.163
"You've gotta get over
and see Carl Reiner.

14:54.163 --> 14:55.797
He wants to read with you

14:55.797 --> 14:57.065
for the part
of Dick Van Dyke's wife."

14:57.065 --> 14:58.667
And I said,
"No, I'm not going. I'm sorry.

14:58.667 --> 15:00.201
I can't take
any more rejections.

15:00.201 --> 15:02.503
You know I'm not
gonna get that part." (CHUCKLES)

15:02.503 --> 15:06.376
<i>I was terrified
because it was my hero,</i>

15:06.376 --> 15:07.342
<i>Carl Reiner,</i>

15:07.342 --> 15:10.746
<i>who was the writer-producer
of this show.</i>

15:10.746 --> 15:12.213
ROB REINER:
The Dick Van Dyke Show

15:12.213 --> 15:15.183
<i>was originally
a show for my father to star in.</i>

15:15.183 --> 15:17.152
- (LAUGHTER)
- ROB: <i>My father had been
on television</i>

15:17.152 --> 15:19.988
<i>for many years with Sid Caesar
in the</i> Show of Shows

15:19.988 --> 15:22.224
<i>- and</i> Caesar's Hour, <i>and then...</i>
- (VOCALIZES)

15:22.224 --> 15:23.491
<i>...when the show was over,</i>

15:23.491 --> 15:26.795
<i>he started writing
a series for himself.</i>

15:26.795 --> 15:28.030
<i>And he played the character</i>

15:28.030 --> 15:30.232
<i>that Dick Van Dyke
plays ultimately.</i>

15:30.232 --> 15:32.067
<i>It was called</i>
Head of the Family.

15:32.067 --> 15:35.470
<i>They'd made the pilot
and it didn't sell.</i>

15:35.470 --> 15:37.973
<i>And he had a meeting
with Sheldon Leonard,</i>

15:37.973 --> 15:39.440
<i>with Danny Thomas and they said,</i>

15:39.440 --> 15:42.978
<i>"The show is great
but we gotta find a new you."</i>

15:42.978 --> 15:45.247
<i>So, they recommended
Dick Van Dyke.</i>

15:45.247 --> 15:47.482
<i>And I'm glad
Dick wound up doing it</i>

15:47.482 --> 15:52.253
<i>because it's what we say,
"We take the comedy of the Jew</i>

15:52.253 --> 15:55.194
<i>and we push it through the goy."</i>

15:56.260 --> 15:59.228
I never knew that
there had been a prior pilot.

15:59.228 --> 16:01.863
So I went over there
and thank God I did.

16:01.863 --> 16:03.532
Do you remember me
grabbing your head?

16:03.532 --> 16:04.699
I think you got scared.

16:04.699 --> 16:06.935
You thought I was gonna--
Because producers in those days,

16:06.935 --> 16:08.637
and maybe still,
have a reputation

16:08.637 --> 16:09.971
of wanting something more than--

16:09.971 --> 16:12.240
- GUEST 1: Bodies. Mm-hmm.
- Yeah, something more
than the talent.

16:12.240 --> 16:14.843
And I heard her,
there was a ping in her voice.

16:14.843 --> 16:16.745
You only read--
I read about 60 girls

16:16.745 --> 16:17.880
and I read
the full script with 'em

16:17.880 --> 16:19.181
- hoping to find something.
- GUEST 2: Yeah.

16:19.181 --> 16:20.716
She read three lines.

16:20.716 --> 16:22.151
I don't like you.

16:22.151 --> 16:25.221
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

16:25.221 --> 16:27.055
At all!

16:27.055 --> 16:28.556
Three simple lines.
There was such a ping

16:28.556 --> 16:30.562
- and an excitement
and a reality to her.
- GUEST 1: Really?

16:32.262 --> 16:34.758
RONA: <i>What attracted you
to Laura Petrie?</i>

16:34.758 --> 16:36.532
The chance to work
with Dick Van Dyke

16:36.532 --> 16:37.532
and Carl Reiner.

16:37.532 --> 16:40.770
I mean... (CHUCKLES)
...what more do you need?

16:40.770 --> 16:43.371
<i>Carl,
it was such a platonic love.</i>

16:43.371 --> 16:46.174
<i>- He was my father, my brother.</i>
- ♪ (GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

16:46.174 --> 16:50.412
MARY: <i>He was my teacher,
my member of the audience</i>

16:50.412 --> 16:54.049
<i>for whom I wanted
to do the scene well.</i>

16:54.049 --> 16:56.718
<i>When I heard him laugh,
that's all I needed.</i>

16:56.718 --> 17:00.155
How often does my boss ask us
over to his house?

17:00.155 --> 17:04.063
How often is one called upon
to be a responsible parent?

17:06.363 --> 17:08.496
ROB:
<i>They just immediately gelled.</i>

17:08.496 --> 17:10.465
- ♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪
- (PAN SIZZLING)

17:10.465 --> 17:12.835
The president of the network
will be there.

17:12.835 --> 17:14.870
ROB: <i>It was seamless.</i>

17:14.870 --> 17:17.309
Well,
then I think you should go.

17:17.875 --> 17:18.874
Oh, I mean it, honey.

17:18.874 --> 17:21.276
There's no sense
both us staying home.

17:21.276 --> 17:23.112
After all,
you have a responsibility

17:23.112 --> 17:25.114
to your work
and I fully understand that.

17:25.114 --> 17:27.650
<i>We just liked each other,
right from the beginning.</i>

17:27.650 --> 17:29.621
- You do?
- Sure I do.

17:30.854 --> 17:33.688
- You don't mind if I go alone?
- Not at all, darling.

17:33.688 --> 17:36.959
<i>There was right away, a sense
of being very comfortable</i>

17:36.959 --> 17:38.860
<i>in the humor that we shared.</i>

17:38.860 --> 17:40.132
Well...

17:41.332 --> 17:43.064
It's just that I couldn't go
to a party

17:43.064 --> 17:45.704
knowing my son was on the verge
of being sick.

17:48.839 --> 17:51.039
I couldn't enjoy myself.

17:51.039 --> 17:53.174
Such chemistry. Such charisma.

17:53.174 --> 17:55.143
I watch the reruns
of <i>The Dick Van Dyke Show</i>

17:55.143 --> 17:56.611
- and I remember every one of--
- (MARY CHUCKLES)

17:56.611 --> 17:58.147
- And I break up, you know?
- MARY: I do too.

17:58.147 --> 17:59.347
I watch them
every once in a while

17:59.347 --> 18:00.582
just before we do our show.

18:00.582 --> 18:02.117
I have a little television set
in the trailer...

18:02.117 --> 18:03.251
- DINAH: Really?
- ...and I catch it.

18:03.251 --> 18:04.353
But it's a little like

18:04.353 --> 18:06.321
the portrait of Dorian Gray
in reverse.

18:06.321 --> 18:08.290
- DINAH: Oh, no. Oh, no.
- I hate it. (LAUGHS)

18:08.290 --> 18:10.291
- I was such a baby then.
- No, we're getting--

18:10.291 --> 18:12.227
- Oh, we're getting better!
- That's true. Yes!

18:12.227 --> 18:13.428
We look much better,
don't you think?

18:13.428 --> 18:14.896
We're not getting older.
We're getting better.

18:14.896 --> 18:17.099
- Right! Better and prettier!
- (AUDIENCE CHEERING, APPLAUDING)

18:17.099 --> 18:19.534
So, eat your hearts out,
you 22-year-olds!

18:19.534 --> 18:21.469
- DINAH: Yes! Let's not forget...
- (CHUCKLES)

18:21.469 --> 18:23.538
- ♪ (WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- MARY: <i>Going in, I knew I was in</i>

18:23.538 --> 18:26.141
<i>with a bunch
of black belts in comedy</i>

18:26.141 --> 18:29.110
<i>and I had
no real experience at it.</i>

18:29.110 --> 18:31.413
<i>I didn't know what I was doing.</i>

18:31.413 --> 18:33.749
DICK VAN DYKE:
<i>There was no hint at all</i>

18:33.749 --> 18:35.150
<i>that Mary could do comedy.</i>

18:35.150 --> 18:37.119
<i>I said she may be
the next Katharine Hepburn</i>

18:37.119 --> 18:39.320
<i>but I don't know... (CHUCKLES)
...about comedy.</i>

18:39.320 --> 18:44.154
MARY: <i>Early on, Carl saw
some spark of humor in me.</i>

18:44.154 --> 18:47.963
<i>He wrote a script called</i>
My Blonde-Haired Brunette.

18:47.963 --> 18:50.398
<i>That was my initiation.</i>

18:50.398 --> 18:54.269
- Oh, Millie, I'm getting old.
- Oh, come on, Laura.

18:54.269 --> 18:56.371
One gray hair
isn't gonna make you old.

18:56.371 --> 18:59.041
Yeah, well,
it's not just a gray hair,

18:59.041 --> 19:01.243
it's Rob's whole attitude
toward me.

19:01.243 --> 19:02.410
We each know exactly

19:02.410 --> 19:04.413
what the other
is gonna think and do.

19:04.413 --> 19:07.015
There just aren't
any more surprises left.

19:07.015 --> 19:10.953
- Well, you have to make them.
- Well, how do you do that?

19:10.953 --> 19:13.255
Well,
whenever Jerry starts taking me

19:13.255 --> 19:15.424
for granted,
I have a simple remedy.

19:15.424 --> 19:17.927
- What?
- I just bleach my hair.

19:17.927 --> 19:19.227
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

19:19.227 --> 19:22.467
Millie, do you think
that if I bleach my hair that--

19:22.900 --> 19:23.903
No I couldn't.

19:25.003 --> 19:26.035
Why not?

19:26.035 --> 19:28.938
Well, I don't think Rob
would approve of me as a blonde.

19:28.938 --> 19:30.640
How does he feel
about Marilyn Monroe

19:30.640 --> 19:31.840
and Brigitte Bardot?

19:31.840 --> 19:35.110
- (AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
- ♪ (SOFT PIANO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

19:35.110 --> 19:36.681
Millie, I'll do it.

19:38.182 --> 19:43.588
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

19:45.824 --> 19:47.957
Why? Why would...

19:47.957 --> 19:51.359
MARY: <i>I had always been
a big fan of Nanette Fabray,</i>

19:51.359 --> 19:52.995
<i>who worked with Carl Reiner</i>

19:52.995 --> 19:55.230
<i>and Sid Caesar
on the</i> Show of Shows.

19:55.230 --> 19:58.033
Twelve long glorious years
of marriage,

19:58.033 --> 20:00.770
twelve years out the window.

20:00.770 --> 20:01.969
(GLASS SHATTERS)

20:01.969 --> 20:04.973
MARY: <i>And I loved her humor.
I loved the way she cried.</i>

20:04.973 --> 20:06.541
Who do you think you are anyway?

20:06.541 --> 20:10.006
- (SOBS HEAVILY)
- (AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

20:10.006 --> 20:11.546
MARY: <i>And so,
when I was called upon</i>

20:11.546 --> 20:14.083
<i>to bring forth the tears
in my scene,</i>

20:14.083 --> 20:15.383
<i>I'm not sure
how much of it</i>

20:15.383 --> 20:18.587
<i>was out and out stolen
from Miss Fabray.</i>

20:18.587 --> 20:19.620
...self?

20:19.620 --> 20:23.225
We are dyeing it back
to its natural color.

20:23.225 --> 20:25.794
Laura's been a blonde
all afternoon.

20:25.794 --> 20:29.164
MARY: <i>And he wants to know why,
what happened?</i>

20:29.164 --> 20:31.733
<i>- And then I try to tell him.</i>
- Honey, why?

20:31.733 --> 20:33.001
(WHIMPERS) "Why?"

20:33.001 --> 20:35.303
(GASPS) Well, yesterday morning,

20:35.303 --> 20:39.474
when I kissed you
and you said, "Don't do that."

20:39.474 --> 20:44.479
And you came down to breakfast
in your yucky shirt

20:44.479 --> 20:46.949
and all you do is...
(MUMBLES INDISTINCTLY)

20:46.949 --> 20:49.918
<i>And that proved
that I could handle comedy.</i>

20:49.918 --> 20:51.686
And the gray hair!

20:51.686 --> 20:54.990
DICK: <i>It was just fascinating
to watch Mary Tyler Moore</i>

20:54.990 --> 20:56.959
<i>just grasp it so quickly.</i>

20:56.959 --> 20:58.527
...yucky! (SOBS)

20:58.527 --> 20:59.661
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING, APPLAUDING)

20:59.661 --> 21:02.164
MARY: <i>A housewife
on a situation comedy</i>

21:02.164 --> 21:04.534
<i>had never been given
the opportunity</i>

21:04.534 --> 21:06.436
<i>to do this kind of stuff.</i>

21:06.436 --> 21:07.803
<i>And it was at that point</i>

21:07.803 --> 21:10.471
<i>that Carl started writing
show after show</i>

21:10.471 --> 21:12.811
<i>and scene after scene
for me to be funny.</i>

21:14.944 --> 21:18.413
ROB: <i>Mary and her
being beautiful and being funny,</i>

21:18.413 --> 21:21.517
<i>that combination was looked at
as being unfeminine.</i>

21:21.517 --> 21:24.620
<i>I mean, Lucy was a rarity</i>

21:24.620 --> 21:27.289
<i>but even Lucy had to resort</i>

21:27.289 --> 21:29.757
<i>to much more
physical kind of stuff.</i>

21:29.757 --> 21:33.698
<i>It wasn't thought of
as a feminine thing to do.</i>

21:34.664 --> 21:36.831
MARY: <i>I was the voice
of the audience.</i>

21:36.831 --> 21:41.773
<i>I was the single voice of sanity
in amongst all these lunatics.</i>

21:44.508 --> 21:46.174
YOUNG LARRY MATHEWS:
Ellen's got a disease.

21:46.174 --> 21:48.911
Well, Ellen's got a temperature.
I wouldn't call it a disease.

21:48.911 --> 21:51.513
Well, whatever she got,
I hope I get it too.

21:51.513 --> 21:53.649
LARRY MATHEWS:
<i>Mary was a combination to me</i>

21:53.649 --> 21:55.684
<i>of a mother figure and a sister.</i>

21:55.684 --> 21:58.553
<i>She would always take time
if she saw me struggling.</i>

21:58.553 --> 22:01.223
<i>It was important to Mary
to have that connection,</i>

22:01.223 --> 22:04.526
<i>since I was playing her son,
to me to be that child of hers.</i>

22:04.526 --> 22:06.628
<i>And I think it did help her
through things.</i>

22:06.628 --> 22:08.563
BEVERLY SANDERS:
<i>She had Richie, her son,</i>

22:08.563 --> 22:13.001
<i>but she and her husband
had separated,</i>

22:13.001 --> 22:14.569
<i>so she had to make a living</i>

22:14.569 --> 22:16.132
<i>- and she did.</i>
- ♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

22:16.132 --> 22:17.639
- Sally, you know the bit.
- I'll do it.

22:17.639 --> 22:19.542
- I need the chair and the hat.
- TV ACTOR:
I got it right here.

22:19.542 --> 22:21.777
(INDISTINCT CLAMORING)

22:21.777 --> 22:24.813
(CHUCKLES)
Oh, your husband's awfully cute.

22:24.813 --> 22:27.550
He must be
a lot of fun to live with.

22:27.550 --> 22:29.718
I laugh all day long.

22:29.718 --> 22:32.387
MARY: <i>Laura actually had
opinions of her own,</i>

22:32.387 --> 22:35.118
<i>and while
she was asserting herself,</i>

22:35.118 --> 22:37.192
<i>she also
didn't make Dick Van Dyke</i>

22:37.192 --> 22:38.859
<i>- look like a dummy.</i>
- ♪ (CHEERFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

22:38.859 --> 22:41.863
MARY: <i>Society's expectations
at that point still said,</i>

22:41.863 --> 22:44.599
<i>"Hey, wait a minute, lady,
you'll only go so far here."</i>

22:44.599 --> 22:47.769
<i>I think we broke new ground
and that was helped</i>

22:47.769 --> 22:50.873
<i>by my insistence
on wearing pants.</i>

22:50.873 --> 22:52.875
<i>I said, "I've seen
all the other actresses</i>

22:52.875 --> 22:54.676
<i>and they're always
running the vacuum</i>

22:54.676 --> 22:58.280
<i>in these little flowered frocks
with high heels on,</i>

22:58.280 --> 22:59.547
<i>and I don't do that,</i>

22:59.547 --> 23:01.582
<i>and I don't know
any of my friends who do that.</i>

23:01.582 --> 23:03.788
<i>So, why don't we try
to make this real?"</i>

23:04.988 --> 23:09.024
BEVERLY: <i>She brought
